questions.scenario:
You are debugging a production issue in a Spring Boot application. A `Task` entity uses a `HashSet` to manage unique assignments. You observe that after calling `repository.save()`, a call to `set.contains(task)` returns `false`, even though the object was just added to the set. 

java
@Entity
public class Task {
    @Id @GeneratedValue
    private Long id;
    private String title;

    @Override
    public int hashCode() {
        return Objects.hash(id);
    }

    @Override
    public boolean equals(Object o) {
        if (this == o) return true;
        if (!(o instanceof Task)) return false;
        Task task = (Task) o;
        return Objects.equals(id, task.id);
    }
}

@Service
public class TaskManager {
    @Transactional
    public void processTask(Set<Task> taskSet, Task newTask) {
        taskSet.add(newTask);
        repository.save(newTask); // Database generates ID here
        if (!taskSet.contains(newTask)) {
            throw new RuntimeException("Task lost in set!");
        }
    }
}

